  "prompt": "Which career is best for me accourding to my birth chart and d10 chart?",
  "response": "Interpreting detailed astrological charts and providing specific career advice requires precise birth details (date, time, and location), and professional expertise in astrology which I can't provide. However, I can give you a general idea of how people might analyze these charts to determine suitable careers.\n\n1. **Sun Sign**: Your sun sign identifies core personality traits, which significantly influence career suitability. For instance, a Leo might excel in leadership roles, while a Pisces might be drawn to creative or healing professions.\n\n2. **Midheaven (10th House)**: This often represents your career and public image. The sign on the Midheaven cusp and any planets in the 10th house can give insight into your career path.\n\n3. **2nd House**: This house covers your personal finances and talents. Examining its ruler and any planets in it can indicate your potential for wealth and the skills you could use to earn money.\n\n4. **6th House**: This house pertains to work, daily routines, and service. The sign and planets here can suggest the environment and type of work you might prefer.\n\n5. **D10 Chart (Dasamsa)**: Specifically in Vedic astrology, the D10 chart provides deeper insights into your career. Analyzing the placement and strength of planets here can help refine your career path.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for professional advice, consider consulting with an experienced astrologer who can examine your birth chart and D10 chart in detail for personalized guidance.",
